@Database "Custom.guide"
@Master "Custom.guide"

@Node Main "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{B}CONTENTS@{UB}

 Wordworth can be customised in many ways to suit
 individual needs. This section will give help on
 how to customise Wordworth.

   @{" The Screen Colours " Link "Custom.guide/CustomColours"}
   @{" The Spell Options " Link "Custom.guide/CustomSpell"}
   @{" The Text Editing Options " Link "Custom.guide/CustomText"}
   @{" The View Options " Link "Custom.guide/CustomView"}

 Using @{" save " Link "Custom.guide/SaveCustom"} will save these settings as the
 default settings.
@EndNode

@Node "CustomColours" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Customising The Screen Colours@{UU}

 By default, Wordworth uses eight colours for
 its screen display. The RGB values of these
 colours can be edited from the "Screen Colours
 Settings" requester ("Change Settings" command,
 Settings menu).

 The screen colours are used for Wordworth's
 icons and requesters. However, if you are
 running Wordworth on the Workbench screen, you
 will not be able to change the colours of the
 Workbench screen from this requester.
@EndNode

@Node "CustomSpell" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Customising The Spell Options@{UU}

 The "Spell Settings" will only be available
 if the Spell Checker module is present.

 User Dictionary entries can be added, edited,
 and deleted from the "Spell Settings" requester
 ("Change Settings" command, Settings menu).
@EndNode

@Node "CustomText" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Customising The Text Options@{UU}

 The "Text Settings" requester ("Change Settings"
 command, Settings menu) allows you to choose
 which editing modifier keys you would like to
 use, the new Wordworth 3 (conforming to
 Commodores guidelines) or the old Wordworth
 keys.

 See @{" Keyboard Control " Link "Keyboard.guide/KeyShortcuts"} for more details on
 what keys to use.


 The cursor blink speed can be selected, and what
 decimal tab character is used.

 When placing a decimal tab on the ruler, the
 characters are aligned according to the character
 specified in the "Decimal Tab Character" text
 gadget.
@EndNode

@Node "CustomView" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Customising The View Options@{UU}

 Choose View from the "Change Settings" list
 (Settings menu) to display a requester from which
 you can adjust several view display:

   You can show/hide the vertical ruler
   You can show/hide the horizontal ruler
   You can show/hide the Ruler Tools
   You can show/hide the Status Bar

 The selected options above will dictate what is
 shown or hidden when choosing the Rulers command
 (Edit menu).

   You can show/hide the margins
   You can show/hide the print borders
   You can show/hide text frames

 From this requester, you can also specify what
 measurement unit is used in requesters, and how
 many sizing handles selected objects will have.
@EndNode

@Node "SaveCustom" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Saving Your Wordworth Customisation@{UU}

 When you choose "Save Settings" (Settings menu),
 all the current settings are saved to the default
 settings file which is used each time you start
 Wordworth.
@EndNode

@Node "CreateIcons" "Customising Wordworth"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 @{U}Create Icons@{UU}
 
 Choose "Create Icons" (Settings menu) to save icons
 with any project (document) or settings file.
@EndNode

@Node "Workbench" "Customising"
@ToC "Ww3.guide/Main"
 Workbench Open/Close
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
 You can save about 40k of memory by choosing the
 Workbench-"Close Workbench" command (Settings menu).

 The Workbench can be re-opened by choosing the
 Workbench-"Open Workbench" command (Settings menu).

 The Workbench can only be closed if you do not have
 any tools or open windows running on the Workbench
 screen.
@EndNode
